This is a full-time position with the Justice & Missions team at The Vine and reports to the Justice & Missions Pastor. The candidate will work in the team responsible for developing and leading initiatives that engage and equip The Vine in its justice advocacy and Missions programs.

This position requires the ability to operate in strategy development, relationship management, event management, and administrative responsibilities. The successful candidate will be able to take initiative and responsibility for key projects and manage ongoing responsibilities.

Job Description

The primary role and responsibilities of the Justice & Missions Associate are as follows:

Contribute to the development of a strategy that furthers The Vine’s justice profile, advocacy efforts, social justice footprint, and theological framework that will be used across Vine ministries and our local community;
Design initiatives that build awareness and mobilise the congregation to practically engage with social and spiritual issues that align with The Vine’s area of focus and the work of our partners;
Produce the flagship Justice Conference Asia (JCA) and other justice-related events that reflect the vision, core values and standards of the Justice Conference;
Assist Justice and Missions Pastor and JCA leadership team in developing strategies to expand the impact of The Justice Conference (TJC) in Asia;
Periodically assist Justice and Missions Pastor to research on justice topics facing Hong Kong;
Assist in planning and organising mission events and oversee local and international missions’ trips;
Develop and grow relationships with external stakeholders and partners (churches, NGOs, influencers);
Recruit and build relationships with volunteers from The Vine;
General administration duties include leading meetings, capturing action steps, managing internal processes, and completing documentation and reporting.

Job Requirement

Strong sense of justice and a passion for social justice issues in Hong Kong and SE Asia;
Knowledge across a range of social, economic, and spiritual developmental issues;
A passion and desire to see every individual flourish spiritually, personally, socially, materially;
Public speaking experience would be beneficial;
Strong organizational and administration skills, including effective time management;
International experience and cross-cultural skills are preferred;
Good command of English (written and spoken). Cantonese is highly desired.

