Qualification & Entry Requirements::
i)     Applicant should posses Professional Membership of the Hong Kong Institute of Landscape Architects (HKILA) and/or be a Registered Landscape Architect (R.L.A.) in Hong Kong as defined under the Landscape Architect Registration Ordinance (Cap. 516); and
ii)    Shall have a minimum 5 years relevant site experience.
iii)   The Resident Landscape Architect shall be full-time engaged on Site starting immediately to end of October 2023 or any extension as necessary.
 
Duties and responsibilities
The duties and responsibilities of the Resident Landscape Architect shall include, but not limited to, the followings:
1.           to coordinate with and report to the Supervising Officer or his representatives all aspects of the Landscape Architectural Works on a daily basis;
2.           to watch and inspect, to test and examine materials used and workmanship employed in the Landscape Architectural Works, to ensure that they are complying with the Employer’s Requirements (ER), specifications, drawings and construction procedure with the assistance of the site supervisory staff;
3.           to identify defective materials and workmanship in the Landscape Architectural Works not complying with the ER, specifications, drawings and construction procedure, and to coordinate appropriate tests on the defective Landscape Architectural Works with the assistance of the site supervisory staff;
4.           to communicate among the Designers, the Contracted Party, the Supervising Officer and his Representative, site supervisory staff and the Specialist Contractors on the Landscape Architectural Works;
5.           to resolve on site Landscape Architectural Works difficulties arising from unforeseen circumstances to allow the landscape architectural works to progress with minimum disruption, and in case of action involving variations to design, consult the Supervising Officer or his representatives;
6.           to report to the Supervising Officer or his representatives any matters of unusual aspect for direction;
7.           to report to the Supervising Officer and his Representative immediately any issues that affect time and quality of the works that need their special attention together with any remedial solution proposed;
8.           to monitoring and reporting of the performance of the Specialist Contractor for landscape work,
9.           to maintain the site record on the Landscape Architectural Works and to coordinate the checking of the Landscape Architectural Works including but not limited to tree preservation, tree transplanting work, plant procurement and tree risk assessment works with the assistance of site supervisory staff;
10.        to monitor the implementation of landscape and visual mitigation measures to ensure compliance with the recommendations of the approved EIA Report;
11.        to monitor the progress and to produce timely information in advance of construction to avoid delay;
12.        to coordinate the Hard and Soft Landscape works requirements in connection to building services and deal with the consequential changes to the Landscape Architectural design and to produce sketch plans and working drawings;
13.        to submit for approval any Landscape Architectural details, in particular any temporary work as required in the Contract;
14.        to attend regular and ad hoc meetings;
15.        to assist the Supervising Officer or his representatives in the investigation and to prepare report on the acceptable or otherwise the use of materials; and
16.        to prepare design, estimate and specification in collaboration with allied disciplines.
17.        to undertake any other duties in connection with site construction activities.
